# Code Conventions

## Configuration
- ALL tunable parameters come from config.yaml. No magic numbers in src/ or scripts/.
- config is loaded once at entry point, passed explicitly. No global config state.
- All paths in config are strings. Convert to pathlib.Path on first use.

## Paths
- Use pathlib.Path everywhere. Never raw strings for file paths.
- Construct paths with / operator: base / "subdir" / "file.npy"

## Type Hints and Docstrings
- All public functions require type hints on all parameters and return values.
- Docstrings: Google style.

## Logging
- Use Python logging module. NEVER use print() in src/ or scripts/.
- Logger: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
- INFO: normal progress. DEBUG: per-frame details. WARNING: recoverable. ERROR: failures.
- Log failed files with full traceback (logging.exception()), not just the filename.

## Error Handling
- Retry logic: use utils.retry() decorator. Never inline retry loops.
- Failed files: log to output_root/failed_files.log with full traceback.

## Progress Bars
- Use tqdm only. Never manual print("Processing x/y...").
- Batch format: "[{elapsed}<{remaining}] {n}/{total} | {rate:.1f} seq/s"
